cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.CYBER, cs.DS, cs.NI 

This paper deals with the analysis of a large-scale social network composed of billions of communication attempts across millions of actors. The paper focuses on investigating the distribution of reciprocity in this network and defines a metric for reciprocity appropriate for weighted networks. The paper also examines the structural features of human communication behavior and relationship formation that either help or hinder the ability of persons to obtain balance in their relationships. Based on this, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences). Additionally, the paper also deals with cybersecurity issues related to human communication networks, which makes cs.CYBER (Cryptography and Security) a likely sub-category. The paper also involves the analysis of large-scale data, which makes cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) possible sub-categories.
